verbose_text: Recent metaanalyses have reported that COPD, a previous hemoglobin level of less than 12.5 g/dL, blood transfusion, previous radiotherapy or chemoradiotherapy, advanced primary tumor, supraglottic subsite, hypopharyngeal tumor site, positive surgical margins, and neck dissection were risk factors for fistula, whereas the suture material was not a significant factor [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR].
